Notebook[{
Cell["SyntheticInfrageometry", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"d543e156-5864-4c4c-8e57-7c85aaa0cd95"],

Cell["\<\
SyntheticInfrageometry organizes Euclidean (metric), path-space (selectors), \
Tarski (betweenness + equidistance), projective (incidence), tropical \
(graph-only convexity), and scene-building layers around multivalued \
constructions on graphs. Curvatures (Forman, Ollivier, Wolfram) supply the \
engines for curvature-minimizing path enumeration. This guide points to the \
main entry points.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1c3839a5-e20d-4124-8242-aa999686bb33"],

